      <heading>[Darith]Thu Feb 21 (Someone)    :: Syllabus</heading>
      <slot>1</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>What follows is a copy of the DL syllabus. This provides
a large framework for what will be taught. I need to
flesh out the weave descriptions, but I plan on making
this into an actual item rather than a post. I just 
wanted to let you know the plan ASAP.

Rules and Regulations
1. Always obey your superiors direct orders (or give
the appearance that you are) unless you want to deal
with the consequences. It is strongly suggested that
you bow if a superior enters the room. The degree of
the bow depends on how high the superior stands in
the chain of command.
2. Do not leave the camp unless you have the rank of
at least Dreadlord Initiate. You are not permitted to
take anyone of a rank lower than that from the camp. 
If you do so and are caught, you will be punished
severely.
3. Recruits are expected to report daily for kitchen
duty as well as cleaning duty in the trolloc pens.
4. The Master Dreadlord's word is law, allowing him/her
to circumvent any rule he/she wishes, or adding as he/she
sees fit. High Dreadlords are also law unto themselves,
but to a lesser degree. Everyone, however, is accountable
to the Dark One himself.
5. Do -NOT- attract notice to yourself or advertise your
true abilities. You are left to your own discretion on 
this matter but know that if you are found to be failing
in your duties or otherwise are displeasing, you will be
dealt with.

Knowledge
1. Trolloc is the preferred language when ordering about
Shadowspawn. That, in addition to a sick displeasure I
derive from it, is the reason why you have to clean those
foul creatures' pens. You'll quickly learn the difference
between 'eat human' and 'too full'.

Recruit
This is the rank at which you will gain almost all of your
formalized training to be a dreadlord. If you have had
emote channeling experience in another guild, be it RT, BT, 
or WT, then you can apply to move forward to Dreadlord
Initiate. The process is simple. I want logs, and lots of them, 
that express to me that you know how to emote channel well.
If you can please me you will pass onto Initiate. If not, you
get to take the lessons. By the way, I want logs of the 
lessons as well. Lessons without logs don't count.

Rules for Recruits
1. No grasping without supervision or permission.
2. No experimenting with weaves until you achieve the rank
of Dreadlord. This means only weave what you are being 
told/taught to weave. To do otherwise is to be punished.

Lessons to be learned OOCly by self-study
1. The use of cemote. The help file can help you with this.
I'd like three examples written up for me and included in 
with one of your lesson logs.
2. The names and purposes of all 5 Powers. There are 
countless resources online as well as through your own 
knowledge on the subject. Explain them to me in a few
sentances each. Also to be included in one of your lesson
logs.
3. The differences between saidar and saidin. &quot;One for the 
woman and one for the man&quot; is not going to be enough, but still
limit your answers to a few sentances. Again, include in one
of the lesson logs.

Lessons to be learned OOCly with a teacher
1. The flame and the void or the flower.
2. Grasping/Releasing
3. The dangers of fatigue while channeling as well as the
dangers of drawing to much Power to you. (burning out)
4. The idea, if not necessarily the action, of linking.

Lessons to be learned ICly with a teacher
1. Wards
2. Fireball/Lightning/Explosion
3. Shield
4. Breakshield
5. Wall of air
6. Club or air
7. Simple healing
8. Wrap
9. Gag
10. Travelling

Travelling is to be the last weave you learn before being 
promoted to Dreadlord Initiate. The others are to be taught
as a bare minimum of what you will need to learn as soon as 
you go out into the world. Remember you need to know the weaves
OOCly before you can know them ICly.

Ranks (Gaining and Losing them)
1. Instead of completing little syllabi for each advancement
in rank, which can be a royal pain in the ass, the promotion
</text>
