    <message>
      <heading>[Darith]Thu Feb 21 (Someone)    :: Syllabus (part II)</heading>
      <slot>2</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>is going to be entirely RP based. This is taking into
consideration the shifting loyalties and power struggles that
constantly go on under the blanket of the Shadow.
2. What this means is that you can advance in one of 
several ways.
a) To take out a person of a rank higher than you through
plotting and other machination. This doesn't mean an all out
battle, this means planning and thinking. Just because you
capped at 274 doesn't mean you are going to be able to fireball
your way to the top. You need alliances of power to wage war.
Get enough power behind you and just maybe a Chosen won't come
after you for killing one of their favorite playthings. Of course,
I am going to need logs, logs, and more logs to verify any
of this.
b) To successfully plan and carry out (at least attempt to carry
it out, it could fail and still count) several plots that either
advance your character in IC power in other guilds, to hurt targets
that are fighting against the Shadow, or just cause general unrest in
the world. Plots that garner significant IC information will also
be rewarded. Know though, that this way of advancement is the slower
of the two. You will have to be recognized for doing your duty. If
a pet performs a trick and the master is not watching, the pet may
not get rewarded. Do the trick over and over again until the Master
sees it and you, the pet, may be well rewarded. Again, I need logs 
and lots of them to prove you are out there working.
3. You can lose rank too if someone below you takes you out or if
someone outperforms you in the field. The Master does like failure,
nor do any of his higher ranking minions. If someone else is better
suited for the job, know that you can and will be replaced.
4. This is a trial system. If it is abused, I'll go back to the
drawing board. I just figure this would be a unique system that was 
bound to spawn RP. A constant struggle is always good to keep
people active.

Darith
</text>
