      <header>Something to avoid</header>
      <slot>8</slot>
      <level>199</level>
      <author>226908</author>
      <date>1055751469</date>
      <authorname>Aidan</authorname>
      <text>
A friendly neighborhood tip on good emote channeling:

Do not under any circumstances use losing control of the One Power as a
way of producing results you could never achieve normally. An example would
be losing control of a shield weave and ending up severing someone or 
losing control of an explosion weave and achieving three times the area of
affect that you normally could. Losing control of the Power does not make
you superman. In fact, the best you can hope for is just losing your grasp.
It is very possible to still or kill yourself by losing control of your
channeling. On top of that, it is incredibly bad RP. Some will think the
following example is an exaggeration, but it is not. Losing control of
channeling to do things you can't normally do is like trying to deadlift
200 pounds more than your max, slipping and falling, and as a result hurling
the weight 50 yards. Flubbing something does not grant you massively
increased strength.

-Aidan
A mostly inactive, but honest about it, DL
</text>
